{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_50","type":"agent_message","text":"I’ve isolated the likely mechanism now: Spotless’ `FeatureClassLoader` does not instantiate the glue classes by normal app-classpath loading. For `com.diffplug.spotless.glue.*`, it asks `getResource(\"<class>.class\")` and then `defineClass(...)`, so if the class bytes are not available as resources in the native image, `loadClass()` still fails even when reflection metadata exists."}}
