{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_86","type":"agent_message","text":"The Graal docs answer the open question directly: `ClassLoader#loadClass(String)` is reflection metadata, but loading classes via non-built-in class loaders is a separate runtime-class-definition problem, and Graal’s documented escape hatch there is predefined-class metadata collected by the agent rather than handwritten reachability entries. That matches the behavior we’re seeing: the extra reflection entries help only until Spotless crosses into actual bytecode loading from its custom loaders."}}
